	<h2>A Brief History of the National Basketball Association</h2>

	<p>The National Basketball Association (NBA) is one of the most
		important professional sport associations in North America. The NBA
		was founded in 1946 in New York City, New York. It is widely
		considered to be the premier men's professional basketball league in
		the world. It has 30 teams which are all based in the United States
		except for 1 that is based in Canada. Over the years, a lot of the NBA
		players have amassed lot of wealth because they are paid handsomely
		than anyone can every dream of earning from regular mearge paying
		jobs. As a result, almost everyone want to become professional
		basketball players. Unfortunately, it requires some supreme basketball
		skills to become a professional basketball player and not everyone is
		so endowed with those unique high sportsmanship skills. Its been over
		70 years now since the founding of the NBA and over that period of
		time, a lot of players have become so famous for being one of the
		greatest basketball players.</p>

	<h2>List of Some of the Famous NBA Players</h2>

	<p>There are so many great and famous NBA players. Some of those
		players achieved their greatness on the basketball court while others
		do so outside of the basketball court by the impact they have on the
		world.</p>
	<br>

